g.text: Allocate major arrays

g.text: pressure periodic boundary conditions

g.text: N_LOOP

g.title: COMMENT_81b4b20+1
g.text: Initialize pressure solver

g.title: COMMENT_81b5800+1
g.text: BC index for Fishpak solver

g.title: COMMENT_81b5800+2
g.text: From Roland Sweet's notes:

g.title: COMMENT_81b5800+3
g.text: Here we use LBC as an example, this is the BC index for the X direction. MBC and NMC are
analogous for the Y and Z directions.

g.title: COMMENT_81b5800+4
g.text: LBC = 0, solution is periodic in X.

g.title: COMMENT_81b5800+5
g.text: LBC = 1, solution is specified at XS (Dirichlet) and XF (Dirichlet).

g.title: COMMENT_81b5800+6
g.text: LBC = 2, solution is specified at XS (Dirichlet) and derivative of solution is specified at XF (Neumann).

g.title: COMMENT_81b5800+7
g.text: LBC = 3, derivative of solution is specified at XS (Neumann) and XF (Neumann).

g.title: COMMENT_81b5800+8
g.text: LBC = 4, derivative of solution is specified at XS (Neumann) and solution is specified at XF (Dirichlet).

g.title: COMMENT_81b5800+9
g.text: LBC = 5, the solution is unspecified at r = RS = 0 and the solution is specified at r = RF.

g.title: COMMENT_81b5800+10
g.text: LBC = 6, if the solution is unspecified at r = RS = 0 and the derivative of the solution with respect to r is specified
at r = RF.

g.title: COMMENT_81b6a00+1
g.text: Look for OPEN vents -- this will change the entire face to DIRICHLET BCs

g.title: DO_81c3440
g.text: VENT_LOOP

g.title: COMMENT_81c5fc0+1
g.text: All interpolated boundaries are Dirichlet
